title: Exploring The Top Cryptocurrencies This Year And Why Big Eyes Coin Should Be On Your Radar - The Cryptonomist
content:
SPONSORED POST*

As the crypto bull market approaches, altcoins are all the rage. Some of the best crypto projects on offer this alt season are Cardano (ADA), Solana (SOL), Cosmos (ATOM), Avalanche (AVAX) and newcomer, Big Eyes Coin (BIG). With a record-breaking presale, Big Eyes Coin has already made quite the impression and is destined for greatness as the presale comes to an end.

Big Eyes Coin Ends Presale With A BIG Bonus Code

Big Eyes Coin is coming to the end of its impressive presale. Having started in late 2022, this new project has raised over $35 million, with presale ending on June 3rd. In the lead-up to the launch, the team are offering investors the chance to receive a 300% bonus with their purchase by using the code END300.

Investors have been flocking to Big Eyes Coin for its unique and innovative features. The impressive ecosystem is designed to self-propagate growth for the community, with NFTs, regular giveaways and a community-centred approach. The project will also have real-world utility to help users make money, and to ensure the longevity of the token.

Cardano Announces Djed Alliance

Cardano is one of the top performing crypto assets, currently ranked 7th by market capitalization and its on-chain activity is on the rise. Cardano’s ecosystem allows developers to create tokens and decentralised applications (dApps) on its scalable blockchain network. The most recent development for the blockchain is the announcement of the Djed alliance which will allow the deployment of stablecoin on the Ethereum compatible sidechain of Cardano. Analysts predict that this could act as a catalyst for Cardano’s growth this year.

Solana Partners With AI

Solana has been one of the top performing cryptos this year, which was a surprise following its poor performance in 2022. Solana is a smart contract platform with an innovative architecture that allows it to process thousands of transactions per second while keeping costs very low. It has one of the most impressive ecosystems in the crypto sector and uses a proof-of-history algorithm with a proof-of-stake consensus mechanism. It has just released a ChaptGPT plugin which allows users to interact with Solana through the AI ChaptGPT chatbox. This is set to simplify many tasks for Solana users including the ability to check wallet balances, make token transfers and buy NFTs on the Solana blockchain.

Cosmos – The Internet Of Blockchains

Known as the ‘internet of blockchains’, Cosmos is an innovative blockchain that is designed to allow blockchain platforms to interoperate with each other. It uses a proof-of-stake consensus which enhances its energy efficiency and can connect with blockchains outside of the Cosmos ecosystem using a protocol called IBC (inter-blockchain communication). Cosmos has been gaining this year, with a 2.48% hike in the last week alone.

Can Avalanche Continue Bullish Momentum?

Avalanche has seen a bullish trend since the start of the year, recording impressive and stable market activity. While it was trading at around $10 at the start of the year, it rallied to $20 in the first few weeks of 2023, before calming down to around $16 today. Avalanche is popular for its ability to deliver trustworthy agreements in a widespread computer network and has been dubbed the ‘Ethereum killer’ for its ability to perform a high level of transactions per second.

The crypto market is constantly evolving with new coins being introduced and new developments in the market. Big Eyes Coin is set to make a big impression when it enters the market, and users have the chance to make a high return on their investments by buying in presale and using the 300% bonus code, END300.
